The paper proposes a model for object recognition that integrates visual attention through a down-sample network and a feedback mechanism. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of a LSTM memory cell and the focus on attention integration and exploitation suggest that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories. Finally, the paper may also belong to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category, as attention mechanisms are commonly used in this field.
